Product description

Why Marfete? Marfete is a brand store focusing on LED light fixture. We not only provide high-quality products, we also provide considerate after-sales service.

Q: Can this lamp match the wall dimmer to adjust the brightness of the light? Such as Lutron, Levition, GE and other brand dimmers？

A: No, the brightness of this light can only be adjusted with the remote control.

Q: Can this lamp be used with AMAZON ALEXA, ECHO, Google home?

A: No, this is not applicable to AMAZON ALEXA, ECHO, Google home.

Q: Is this lamp battery powered?

A: The lamp is not battery-powered. The product needs to be connected to AC90-265V to get work (only the remote control is battery-powered).

Q: All of the remotes come with the lights can control the lights each other?

I purchased 2 pack of your lights and installed the 2 lights in separate rooms, and the remotes for each of them controls both lights at the same time. What can we do to have the remote separately adjust just one light ?

A: This item is normally designed "1 remote for multiple lights". To control the single light with 1 remote control at the same room, you may need to do the pairing code procedure for the single light before using it to control the light. Matching method:

-----------

1. Turn off all of the lights with the wall switch.

2. Turn on the single light with the wall switch, meanwhile, keeping pressing the "On/Off" button of the single remote control for 3 seconds (the code need be paired within three seconds after the light turned on).

3. The light will flash once indicating that the code has been successfully paired. Otherwise, it is failed to be paired, you may try the 1&2 procedure again.

-----------

Main Light

The Color Temperature: 3000k - 6500k; The Brightness: 10%-100%.

You can choose the brightness and type of light fixture from cool, day or warm white light.

Main Light + RGB Light Lit Up at the Same Time

7 RGB Static Colours

Multi colour lighting also very nice to give a multi colour mood light.

There's the RGB color changing light that gives off a relaxing atmosphere, it has 7 colours that can be switched easily with the remote control.

2 Rgb Cycle Modes (fast/ slow)

There are the usual red blue green yellow purple, they can cycle through.

Night Light

You can adjust one of the modes as a night light for your children or parents overnight and for when you get up early in the dark.

Marfete RGB Close to Ceiling Light

Fun, Bright, and the Color Changing

1.The RGB side light & the regular light can be on at the same time.

2.RGB Side Light -- 7 RGB colors + 2 RGB cycle modes fast/ slow.

3.Regular Light -- 3000k~6500k color temperature + 10%~100% brightness dimming + night light.

2.4G Remote Control

1.Adjust color temperature, brightness, rgb color, night, 30s off-delay.

2.No need to point at the light to remote (arbitrary direction).

3.Remote control signal range: 393.7 inches/ 10m.

4.Batteries are not included.

      "Code pairing for multiple lights" .You may try the following method :
      To control the multiple lights with 1 remote control at the same time, you may need to do the pairing code procedure before using it to control the light.
      - Matching method:
      -----------
      1. Turn off all of the lights at the same time with the wall switch. (all of the lights install in the same room)
      multiple.
      2.Turn on all of the lights at the same time with the wall switch, meanwhile, keeping pressing the "On/Off" button of the single 1 remote control for 3 seconds (the code need be paired within three seconds after the light turned on).
      3. All of the lights will flash once indicating that the code has been successfully paired. Otherwise, it is failed to be paired, you may try the 1&2 procedure again.

      1. The installation was fairly straightforward. It took me a bit longer because I initially thought the "height increase pads" needed to be attached directly to the ceiling first, which made it difficult to align them properly. The correct method is to attach the pads to the plastic base first, and then secure the entire assembly to the ceiling with screws. I also had to connect a third copper wire to the metal box inside the ceiling.

      2. The functionality is impressive. It only took about 30 seconds to figure out how to turn off the white light and keep the LED on—you just need to use the power button on the remote.

OK if the LED RGB light did not work sometimes but it will do a dim light mode too. Have to grab the remote and adjust to see. If this thing would keep the mode locked in it would be a winner for sure.
